HEADWORD: Procurement
<hw>Pro*cure"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of procuring or obtaining; obtainment;
attainment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Efficient contrivance; management; agency.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They think it done⟦br⟧
By her <qex>procurement</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Procurer</ent>⟦br⟧
